      Methods in main.com.galaxy.utilities.validators that throw CustomException 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      private static void RomanNumberValidator.checkIfCurrentCharAllowedToRepeat(java.lang.Character c)
      Currently D, V, L are not allowed to repeat.
      private static boolean RomanNumberValidator.isRomanNumeral(java.lang.String roman)
      Checks if input is a Roman numeral
      private static boolean RomanNumberValidator.validateRepeats(java.lang.String romanString)
      Performs below validations:
      1- The symbols "I", "X", "C", and "M" can be repeated three times in succession, but no more.
      private static boolean RomanNumberValidator.validateSubtracts(java.lang.String roman)
      Performs below validations:
      1- "I" can be subtracted from "V" and "X" only.
      2- "X" can be subtracted from "L" and "C" only.
      3- "C" can be subtracted from "D" and "M" only.
      4- "V", "L", and "D" can never be subtracted.
      5- Only one small-value symbol may be subtracted from any large-value symbol.
